15/07/2005
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- The Hellenic Railways Organisation will run high-speed lines from Thessaloniki to Skopje, Belgrade and Bucharest, Transportation and Communications Minister Mihalis Liapis announced on Wednesday (13 July). 
Similar trains are already running to Istanbul and Sofia. 
In the case of Istanbul, the introduction of new lines cut travel time by three hours. 
(A1 TV - 15/07/05; ANA - 14/07/05)
